<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="75" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dun</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 76.]</seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-17"><hi rend="italic">November 17,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Japanese minister for foreign affairs requests in the event of China desiring
                        to approach Japan upon the subject of peace it shall be done though the
                        legation of the United States at Peking.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>